WEBVTT

00:09.810 --> 00:11.245
- * ONE, TWO, THREE, FOUR

00:11.279 --> 00:13.214
* ONE, TWO, THREE,
FOUR, FIVE, SIX *

00:13.247 --> 00:14.515
* SHAKE IT, DUDE

00:14.548 --> 00:22.523
*

00:32.300 --> 00:34.068
* ONE, TWO, THREE

00:34.102 --> 00:37.405
*

00:38.706 --> 00:40.774
[treadmill whirring]

00:40.808 --> 00:43.777
[rock music]

00:43.811 --> 00:51.752
*

00:58.326 --> 01:01.095
[phone ringing]

01:03.497 --> 01:04.832
- HELLO?

01:04.865 --> 01:06.800
[treadmill whirring]

01:11.605 --> 01:13.207
[beeps]

01:17.411 --> 01:19.213
- WHO WAS THAT?

01:19.247 --> 01:21.349
- BRIAN.
[rips tape]

01:21.382 --> 01:23.651
- AND WHAT DID HE HAVE TO SAY?

01:23.684 --> 01:26.587
- HE DIDN'T SAY ANYTHING,
HE JUST HUNG UP.

01:26.620 --> 01:28.322
- SO HOW DO YOU KNOW
IT WAS HIM?

01:28.356 --> 01:29.823
- HIS BREATHING.

01:29.857 --> 01:31.225
HE'S GOT THIS
FUNNY LITTLE WHEEZE

01:31.259 --> 01:33.194
FROM HIS DEVIATED SEPTUM.

01:33.227 --> 01:36.164
- HMM, IT'S NOT THE ONLY THING
ABOUT HIM THAT'S DEVIATED.

01:38.366 --> 01:39.600
- I WONDER WHAT HE WANTED.

01:39.633 --> 01:42.436
- HUH, LET'S SEE,
TO, UH, COME OVER HERE,

01:42.470 --> 01:44.472
THROW HIMSELF AT YOUR FEET
AND BEG FORGIVENESS?

01:44.505 --> 01:46.640
- BRIAN DOESN'T DO APOLOGIES.

01:46.674 --> 01:49.310
- WELL, HE SHOULD,
AFTER WHAT HE DID.

01:49.343 --> 01:50.578
- IT'S TOO LATE.

01:50.611 --> 01:53.247
HE PUSHED TOO HARD.

01:53.281 --> 01:56.417
AND NOW THE GAME IS OVER.

01:56.450 --> 01:58.486
- I KNOW.

01:58.519 --> 01:59.753
AND I'M SORRY.

01:59.787 --> 02:01.589
- IT DOESN'T MATTER.

02:01.622 --> 02:03.891
I'M GOING TO BE TOO BUSY
BEING HAPPY.

02:03.924 --> 02:05.826
I WON'T EVEN HAVE TIME
TO THINK ABOUT IT.

02:05.859 --> 02:07.195
- WHO EVER WOULD
HAVE BELIEVED,

02:07.228 --> 02:08.862
YOU, A MARRIED LADY?

02:08.896 --> 02:12.466
- I PREFER THE TERM
"DOMESTIC PARTNER."

02:12.500 --> 02:13.601
- [snickers]

02:13.634 --> 02:15.736
- WHO CARES WHAT IT'S CALLED,
AS LONG AS I HAVE DAVID?

02:15.769 --> 02:17.705
- AND I HAVE THE APARTMENT!

02:17.738 --> 02:18.939
- [chuckles]

02:18.972 --> 02:20.508
NOW YOU CAN BRING HOME
ALL THE TRICKS YOU WANT

02:20.541 --> 02:22.243
AND YOU DON'T HAVE TO WORRY
ABOUT DISTURBING ME.

02:22.276 --> 02:24.745
"TRY NOT TO SCREAM SO LOUD
WHEN YOU COME.

02:24.778 --> 02:26.647
WE'LL WAKE UP MICHAEL!"

02:26.680 --> 02:29.650
- WELL, WE'LL SEE ABOUT THAT.

02:33.654 --> 02:37.191
- WELL, I GUESS THIS IS IT.

02:37.225 --> 02:39.927
OH! I ALMOST FORGOT.

02:39.960 --> 02:43.797
- HERE,
LET ME HELP YOU.

02:52.973 --> 02:55.909
- I GUESS NOW THIS IS IT.

02:57.545 --> 03:00.348
- GOOD LUCK, SWEETIE.

03:00.381 --> 03:03.817
AND REMEMBER, YOU ALWAYS HAVE
A PLACE TO COME BACK TO.

03:03.851 --> 03:06.387
- THAT'S VERY NICE OF YOU,
EMMETT.

03:06.420 --> 03:08.589
ESPECIALLY SINCE I'M STILL
PAYING HALF THE RENT.

03:08.622 --> 03:11.425
- [chuckles]

03:11.459 --> 03:13.594
- CAPTAIN ASTRO USES
HIS MAGICAL FISTING POWER--

03:13.627 --> 03:15.529
- QUIT IT. IT'S TOO EARLY
FOR FISTING.

03:15.563 --> 03:17.431
- NO, IT IS NEVER TOO EARLY
FOR FISTING.

03:17.465 --> 03:19.600
- THE GYM CALLED YOU,
AND YOUR TAILOR CALLED AGAIN.

03:19.633 --> 03:20.868
AND RYDER WANTS YOU--

03:20.901 --> 03:22.636
- OH, FUCK THE GYM,
FUCK THE TAILOR,

03:22.670 --> 03:24.572
AND FUCK RYDER.

03:24.605 --> 03:26.840
COULD YOU PLEASE GET ME
SOME ASPIRIN OR SOMETHING?

03:26.874 --> 03:28.476
I HAVE A BITCH OF A HEADACHE.

03:28.509 --> 03:30.744
- [exhales]

03:30.778 --> 03:32.746
OKAY.

03:35.583 --> 03:37.718
IT'S BEEN A WEEK
SINCE THE USUAL PHONE CALLS

03:37.751 --> 03:39.019
FROM MICHAEL
EVERY FIVE MINUTES.

03:39.052 --> 03:42.823
IS HE AWAY OR SOMETHING?

03:42.856 --> 03:45.793
- YEAH, YOU COULD SAY THAT.

03:50.498 --> 03:52.833
[cell phone rings]

03:54.668 --> 03:55.769
- TED SCHMIDT.

03:55.803 --> 03:58.372
- BRIAN.

03:58.406 --> 03:59.773
- BRIAN WHO?

03:59.807 --> 04:02.810
- BRIAN WHO-DO-YOU-THINK?
THAT'S WHO.

04:02.843 --> 04:05.546
- OH. I DIDN'T RECOGNIZE
YOUR VOICE.

04:05.579 --> 04:07.748
YOU KNOW, I DON'T THINK
YOU'VE EVER CALLED ME.

04:07.781 --> 04:09.350
- WELL, TODAY'S YOUR LUCKY DAY.

04:09.383 --> 04:10.784
- I'M NOT TALKING TO YOU,
REMEMBER?

04:10.818 --> 04:13.587
- YEAH, RIGHT. UH, SO WHAT
ARE YOU DOING TONIGHT?

04:13.621 --> 04:14.888
- I HAVEN'T THOUGHT ABOUT IT.

04:14.922 --> 04:16.457
- WELL, THINK ABOUT IT
AND DECIDE

04:16.490 --> 04:19.360
IF YOU WANT TO HANG OUT.

04:19.393 --> 04:20.628
- WITH YOU?

04:20.661 --> 04:22.029
- YOU SOUND SURPRISED.

04:22.062 --> 04:25.466
- UH, NO. SURPRISED
WOULD BE IF I WON THE LOTTERY.

04:25.499 --> 04:26.700
OR IF AN ASTEROID
HIT THE EARTH,

04:26.734 --> 04:29.002
OR IF RICHARD SIMMONS
WAS STRAIGHT.

04:29.036 --> 04:30.771
NO, TRY DUMBSTRUCK.

04:30.804 --> 04:33.607
- SO YOU'RE NOT BUSY?

04:33.641 --> 04:34.808
- DO YOU HAVE TO ASK?

04:34.842 --> 04:37.345
- WOODY'S. AFTER WORK.

04:44.017 --> 04:48.789
- HE WANTS ME TO MEET HIM
AT WOODY'S TO HANG OUT.

04:48.822 --> 04:52.760
- GOD, HE MUST
REALLY BE DESPERATE.

04:52.793 --> 04:55.062
I-I DIDN'T MEAN IT
LIKE THAT.

04:55.095 --> 04:56.897
- NOW THAT HE AND MICHAEL
ARE NO LONGER FRIENDS,

04:56.930 --> 04:58.966
MY GUESS IS IS THAT
HE NEEDS SOMEBODY NEW

04:58.999 --> 05:00.468
TO TAKE FOR GRANTED.

05:00.501 --> 05:02.803
SO, NATURALLY,
HE THOUGHT OF ME.

05:02.836 --> 05:04.738
- YOU'RE NOT ACTUALLY
CONSIDERING GOING, ARE YOU?

05:04.772 --> 05:08.442
- WELL, MAYBE I CAN RESOLVE
THE GREAT MICHAEL CONFLICT,

05:08.476 --> 05:09.710
AND WIN THE NOBEL PEACE PRIZE

05:09.743 --> 05:12.079
AND SCORE WITH
ONE OF BRIAN'S REJECTS.

05:12.112 --> 05:13.581
- [groans]

05:13.614 --> 05:16.584
49, 50.

05:16.617 --> 05:17.818
[deep breath]

05:17.851 --> 05:21.021
GOD, I HATE MY ABS.

05:21.054 --> 05:23.791
- I LOVE YOUR ABS.

05:25.859 --> 05:27.461
I MEAN YOU.

05:27.495 --> 05:28.962
- HE MEANS YOU.

05:28.996 --> 05:30.364
- YOU'RE EMMETT, RIGHT?

05:30.398 --> 05:31.799
- RIGHT.

05:31.832 --> 05:33.967
- YOU WORK AT TORSO, RIGHT?
- RIGHT.

05:34.001 --> 05:36.404
- AND YOUR DENTIST
IS DR. FELDMAN, RIGHT?

05:36.437 --> 05:38.706
- RIGHT, HOW DO YOU KNOW
WHO MY DENTIST IS?

05:38.739 --> 05:40.441
- I WAS IN HIS OFFICE
LAST WEEK.

05:40.474 --> 05:42.843
I HAD THE APPOINTMENT
RIGHT AFTER YOU.

05:42.876 --> 05:44.111
AND BY THE WAY,
I LOVE THE SPACE

05:44.144 --> 05:46.580
BETWEEN YOUR TEETH.

05:46.614 --> 05:47.915
I'M BEAU.

05:47.948 --> 05:49.917
- THAT'S FRENCH FOR "BEAUTIFUL."
- I KNOW.

05:49.950 --> 05:52.586
- AND I'VE ALWAYS THOUGHT
YOU WERE KIND OF, UH, CUTE.

05:52.620 --> 05:54.955
- YOU HAVE?
- YEAH.

05:54.988 --> 05:56.123
AND I WAS WONDERING,

05:56.156 --> 05:57.591
IF MAYBE YOU'D LIKE
TO GO OUT SOMETIME.

05:57.625 --> 05:59.760
- AS IF YOU NEED TO ASK.

05:59.793 --> 06:00.928
- I'D LOVE TO...

06:00.961 --> 06:02.129
- AS IF HE'D SAY NO.

06:02.162 --> 06:04.598
- ONLY I CAN'T.

06:04.632 --> 06:05.899
- WHAT?

06:05.933 --> 06:07.701
- I-I CAN'T.

06:07.735 --> 06:09.770
BUT THANKS FOR ASKING.

06:09.803 --> 06:13.373
- MAYBE SOME OTHER TIME, THEN.

06:16.076 --> 06:18.746
- ARE YOU OUT OF YOUR MIND?

06:18.779 --> 06:21.081
GUYS LIKE US DO NOT
TURN DOWN GUYS LIKE HIM.

06:21.114 --> 06:22.750
YOU HAVE ACTED
IN FLAGRANT VIOLATION

06:22.783 --> 06:24.918
OF THE ENTIRE GAY
SOCIAL STRUCTURE.

06:24.952 --> 06:26.520
THEY'RE GOING TO VOTE YOU OUT
OF THE BROTHERHOOD.

06:26.554 --> 06:28.856
- LET 'EM. I MADE A PROMISE
TO GOD, REMEMBER?

06:28.889 --> 06:30.057
THAT IF
I TESTED NEGATIVE--

06:30.090 --> 06:31.992
- I KNOW, YOU'D NEVER HAVE SEX
WITH ANOTHER MAN, I KNOW.

06:32.025 --> 06:34.928
BUT Y-YOU'RE FINE.
- IT DOESN'T MATTER.

06:34.962 --> 06:36.497
I NEVER WANT TO GO THROUGH
THE HELL

06:36.530 --> 06:38.766
THAT I WENT THROUGH AGAIN,
AND I WON'T.

06:38.799 --> 06:42.570
BECAUSE SOMEONE KEPT
HIS PART OF THE BARGAIN.

06:42.603 --> 06:45.539
NOW IT'S MY TURN
TO KEEP MINE.

06:47.240 --> 06:49.042
- HEY.

06:49.076 --> 06:50.811
I DIDN'T
HEAR YOU COME IN.

06:50.844 --> 06:52.079
MMM.

06:52.112 --> 06:53.647
[baby crying]

06:53.681 --> 06:54.915
OH.
[shushes]

06:54.948 --> 06:57.918
I JUST PUT GUS TO BED.

06:57.951 --> 06:59.186
- IT'S TOO LATE
TO SEE HIM THEN, HUH?

06:59.219 --> 07:01.955
- OH, YOU CAN SEE HIM
IN THE MORNING.

07:01.989 --> 07:03.524
- HE'S ASLEEP WHEN I LEAVE.

07:03.557 --> 07:04.658
- WELL, MAYBE
YOU COULD LEAVE LATER,

07:04.692 --> 07:06.794
OR EVEN
TAKE THE AFTERNOON OFF.

07:06.827 --> 07:07.995
- THE POINT OF MY
WORKING LONGER DAYS

07:08.028 --> 07:11.765
IS SO YOU CAN STAY HOME.

07:11.799 --> 07:13.534
- I APPRECIATE
HOW HARD YOU WORK.

07:13.567 --> 07:15.969
- WELL, IT WOULD BE NICE
IF YOU SHOWED IT.

07:16.003 --> 07:18.071
- I THOUGHT I DID.

07:18.105 --> 07:21.074
AND, UH, I'M WORKING TOO--

07:21.108 --> 07:23.010
TAKING CARE OF OUR SON.

07:23.043 --> 07:25.513
- YOUR SON AND BRIAN'S.
I JUST PAY THE BILLS.

07:25.546 --> 07:27.681
- OH, ARE WE REALLY
GOING TO GO THROUGH THIS AGAIN?

07:27.715 --> 07:29.883
- NAH, LET'S PRETEND
EVERYTHING'S FINE.

07:29.917 --> 07:32.052
- I DIDN'T SAY
EVERYTHING'S FINE.

07:32.085 --> 07:35.055
I JUST DON'T FEEL THE NEED
TO CONSTANTLY TALK ABOUT IT.

07:35.088 --> 07:37.224
- WELL, I'M JEWISH
AND AFTER NEO-NAZIS,

07:37.257 --> 07:39.560
THERE'S NOTHING THE JEWS FEAR
MORE THAN SILENCE.

07:39.593 --> 07:40.794
- WELL, I'M NOT LIKE THAT.

07:40.828 --> 07:42.963
I DON'T HAVE THE NEED
TO CONSTANTLY EXPRESS

07:42.996 --> 07:44.064
EVERYTHING
THAT I'M FEELING.

07:44.097 --> 07:45.232
- WELL, I WISH YOU'D TRY.

07:45.265 --> 07:47.067
'CAUSE AFTER THAT FIASCO
AT BRIAN'S,

07:47.100 --> 07:49.269
YOU'VE TURNED OFF TO ME
PHYSICALLY, EMOTIONALLY--

07:49.302 --> 07:51.104
- AS USUAL,
YOU'RE CATASTROPHIZING,

07:51.138 --> 07:52.873
TURNING EVERY LITTLE SLIGHT
INTO A REJECTION.

07:52.906 --> 07:54.241
- YOU NEVER WANT
TO MAKE LOVE,

07:54.274 --> 07:55.843
YOU BARELY WANT
TO HAVE A DISCUSSION.

07:55.876 --> 07:58.712
- HAS IT EVER OCCURRED TO YOU
THAT I MIGHT BE TIRED?

07:58.746 --> 07:59.913
- WELL, I'M TIRED TOO.

07:59.947 --> 08:02.583
I'M TIRED OF TRYING
TO GET THROUGH TO YOU,

08:02.616 --> 08:05.285
OF FIGURING OUT WHAT THE HELL
I DID WRONG,

08:05.318 --> 08:07.020
OF WONDERING WHY
INSTEAD OF FEELING CLOSER

08:07.054 --> 08:10.490
THAN WE'VE EVER BEEN,
I HAVE NEVER FELT MORE ALONE.

08:15.663 --> 08:19.567
AREN'T YOU
GOING TO SAY ANYTHING?

08:19.600 --> 08:20.701
- [clears throat]

08:20.734 --> 08:22.936
WHAT WOULD YOU
LIKE FOR DINNER?

08:22.970 --> 08:25.005
I CAN HEAT UP
SOME POT ROAST.

08:25.038 --> 08:28.909
- [scoffs]

08:28.942 --> 08:31.845
- SHOOTERS.

08:34.782 --> 08:36.183
SHOOTER?

08:36.216 --> 08:38.686
CRANTINI SHOOTERS.

08:38.719 --> 08:41.555
ANYBODY?

08:41.589 --> 08:43.523
OH, COME ON, YOU GUYS.

08:45.793 --> 08:49.062
- SO, HOW WAS WORK?

08:49.096 --> 08:51.932
- FAT MARLEY HAD THIS
REALLY INCREDIBLE HICKEY.

08:51.965 --> 08:53.567
AND THERE WAS A SALE
ON PROTEIN POWDER,

08:53.601 --> 08:54.968
SO EVERY QUEEN
IN THE CITY WAS THERE,

08:55.002 --> 08:57.170
EXCEPT FOR YOU, OF COURSE.

08:57.204 --> 08:58.238
- BORING.

08:58.271 --> 09:01.074
WORK WAS BORING.

09:01.108 --> 09:02.843
HOW ABOUT YOU?

09:02.876 --> 09:04.344
- DON'T TELL ME.
YOU TOOK THE CLIENT

09:04.377 --> 09:06.980
TO THIS REALLY
FANCY RESTAURANT FOR LUNCH,

09:07.014 --> 09:10.050
AND THERE WAS THIS REALLY
HOT WAITER AND HE--

09:10.083 --> 09:12.052
HE SIGNALLED FOR YOU
TO MEET HIM IN THE LINEN CLOSET

09:12.085 --> 09:13.987
AND HE GAVE YOU
THIS AMAZING BLOW JOB,

09:14.021 --> 09:15.122
AND THEN YOU
WENT BACK TO THE TABLE

09:15.155 --> 09:16.990
AND THE CLIENT NEVER KNEW.

09:17.024 --> 09:20.628
- HOW'D YOU GUESS?

09:20.661 --> 09:23.797
- I ASKED YOU ABOUT WORK.

09:23.831 --> 09:25.666
- UH, I TOOK A CLIENT
TO LUNCH

09:25.699 --> 09:27.835
AND THE WAITER BLEW ME
IN THE LINEN CLOSET.

09:27.868 --> 09:28.969
- REALLY?

09:29.002 --> 09:31.071
- LIAR! YOU'RE SUCH A LIAR.

09:31.104 --> 09:33.607
- [chuckles]

09:33.641 --> 09:35.108
- [sighs]

09:38.679 --> 09:39.847
- SO, HAVE YOU TALKED TO HIM?

09:39.880 --> 09:41.649
- WHO?

09:41.682 --> 09:43.083
- MICHAEL.

09:43.116 --> 09:44.752
- WHAT FOR?

09:44.785 --> 09:46.720
- OH, FOR NO OTHER REASON
THAN HE'S YOUR BEST FRIEND.

09:46.754 --> 09:49.356
- WAS MY BEST FRIEND.

09:52.392 --> 09:53.894
- WHY DON'T YOU JUST CALL HIM?

09:53.927 --> 09:55.763
- I TOLD YOU.

09:55.796 --> 09:58.365
HE'S OUT OF MY LIFE
AND I'M OUT OF HIS.

09:58.398 --> 10:03.003
SO WOULD YOU PLEASE
SHUT THE FUCK UP ABOUT IT?

10:03.036 --> 10:04.738
- HEY.

10:04.772 --> 10:08.075
HOW'S IT GOING?

10:08.108 --> 10:11.011
- I'M NOT INTERESTED.

10:14.682 --> 10:16.049
- HOWEVER, UH,

10:16.083 --> 10:20.287
I AM AVAILABLE FOR SAFE SEX
AND ESTATE PLANNING.

10:23.991 --> 10:28.195
- ACTUALLY, I DO HAVE
SOME INVESTMENT QUESTIONS.

10:35.969 --> 10:38.872
- WELL, I'LL TELL YOU WHAT.

10:38.906 --> 10:42.275
YOU HELP ME
DIVERSIFY MY PORTFOLIO,

10:42.309 --> 10:45.278
I'LL HELP DIVERSIFY YOURS.

10:49.449 --> 10:52.052
- THAT'S THE LAST ONE.

10:52.085 --> 10:54.254
- YOU'RE SURE?

10:54.287 --> 10:55.422
- WELL, YEAH,
FOR THE MOST PART.

10:55.455 --> 10:57.157
I MEAN, I'M GONNA GO BACK

10:57.190 --> 10:58.826
AND GET THE REST TOMORROW.

10:58.859 --> 11:01.061
- THE REST?

11:01.094 --> 11:02.763
YOU GOT A LOT OF STUFF.

11:02.796 --> 11:06.366
- WELL, YOU KNOW,
IF I FIND SOMETHING I LIKE,

11:06.399 --> 11:09.770
I HOLD ON TO IT, YOU KNOW,
FOR KEEPS.

11:09.803 --> 11:12.039
- I HOPE THAT APPLIES TO ME,
I HOPE THAT APPLIES TO ME.

11:12.072 --> 11:14.141
I HOPE THAT APPLIES TO ME.
- ESPECIALLY TO YOU.

11:14.174 --> 11:15.743
- [chuckles]

11:15.776 --> 11:16.910
- SO WHERE SHOULD I PUT IT?

11:16.944 --> 11:19.079
- WHEREVER YOU WANT, BABY.

11:19.112 --> 11:21.982
- I MEANT MY STUFF.

11:22.015 --> 11:26.053
- YOU DECIDE.
IT'S OUR PLACE NOW.

11:26.086 --> 11:27.855
- GREAT.

11:27.888 --> 11:30.190
UM--

11:30.223 --> 11:33.226
- BUT WHY DON'T YOU
WAIT TILL TOMORROW MORNING?

11:33.260 --> 11:34.728
'CAUSE I GOT PLANS
FOR US TONIGHT.

11:34.762 --> 11:36.063
- OH?
- OH.

11:36.096 --> 11:38.832
- OOH.

11:38.866 --> 11:41.835
[techno music]

11:41.869 --> 11:49.843
*

12:00.220 --> 12:03.857
- SO, YOU SURE
YOU'RE OKAY GETTING HOME?

12:03.891 --> 12:05.525
- YEAH, I KNOW THE WAY.

12:05.558 --> 12:07.094
- RIGHT.

12:07.127 --> 12:15.102
*

12:32.219 --> 12:35.923
[both panting]

12:38.859 --> 12:41.829
- [moans]

13:07.988 --> 13:12.292
[moans]

13:12.325 --> 13:14.361
[both panting]

13:36.616 --> 13:40.153
- [moans]

13:44.491 --> 13:46.259
- OH, MAN.

13:46.293 --> 13:49.262
[both panting]

14:12.185 --> 14:14.054
- I'M SO LUCKY.

14:14.087 --> 14:16.223
- WHY IS THAT?

14:16.256 --> 14:18.158
- WELL, NORMALLY
ABOUT THIS TIME

14:18.191 --> 14:19.927
I'D BE COMING OUT OF WOODY'S,

14:19.960 --> 14:21.328
WAITING IN THE JEEP
FOR BRIAN

14:21.361 --> 14:22.529
TO FINISH
GETTING A BLOW JOB

14:22.562 --> 14:26.533
SO I COULD DRIVE HIM HOME.

14:26.566 --> 14:29.502
- AND INSTEAD?

14:29.536 --> 14:32.472
- AND INSTEAD I'M HERE,
WITH YOU.

14:36.043 --> 14:38.045
- I'M LUCKY TOO.

14:40.313 --> 14:43.951
I LOVE YOU, MICHAEL.

14:43.984 --> 14:51.925
*

14:53.293 --> 14:56.296
- MIKEY?

15:10.110 --> 15:12.012
- HEY, SLEEPYHEAD.

15:12.045 --> 15:14.547
- WHAT ARE YOU DOING
UP SO EARLY?

15:14.581 --> 15:17.450
- WELL, I COULDN'T WAIT
TO UNPACK MY STUFF.

15:17.484 --> 15:20.453
SO WHAT DO YOU THINK?

15:25.025 --> 15:27.294
- IT--IT'S, UH--

15:27.327 --> 15:30.197
IT'S GREAT.

15:30.230 --> 15:33.333
I-I ESPECIALLY LIKE
THE, UM--

15:33.366 --> 15:36.236
WHERE YOU'VE--
THE, UH, THE PUTTING OF--

15:36.269 --> 15:37.704
WHAT'S HIS NAME?

15:37.737 --> 15:39.572
- CAPTAIN ASTRO.

15:39.606 --> 15:42.642
YEAH, I WASN'T SURE HOW YOU
WERE GOING TO FEEL ABOUT THAT.

15:42.675 --> 15:44.277
- OH, IT ADDS A REAL,

15:44.311 --> 15:48.615
UH, WHIMSICAL TOUCH.

15:48.648 --> 15:51.351
- I'M STILL NOT SURE WHERE
TO PUT MY TOY ROBOTS.

15:53.086 --> 15:55.455
- WELL, I'M SURE
YOU'LL FIND THE PERFECT PLACE.

15:55.488 --> 15:58.058
NOW COME ON,
LET'S GO BACK TO BED.

15:58.091 --> 16:00.560
- BED?
SOME OF US HAVE TO WORK.

16:00.593 --> 16:02.195
- IT'S SATURDAY.

16:02.229 --> 16:04.631
- THE BIG "Q" NEVER CLOSES.

16:04.664 --> 16:06.466
- I WAS KIND OF HOPING
WE'D JUST KICK BACK

16:06.499 --> 16:09.569
AND WATCH THE GAME.

16:09.602 --> 16:12.605
- WELL, I'VE NEVER REALLY
BEEN INTO WATCHING THE GAME...

16:12.639 --> 16:14.474
[robot whirring]

16:14.507 --> 16:16.443
OR SATURDAYS.

16:16.476 --> 16:18.345
- YOU HAVE SOMETHING
AGAINST SATURDAYS?

16:18.378 --> 16:19.579
- [chuckles]

16:19.612 --> 16:22.182
WELL, THAT WAS THE DAY
THAT ALL THE KIDS

16:22.215 --> 16:24.051
DID STUFF WITH THEIR DADS.

16:24.084 --> 16:26.553
AND I DIDN'T HAVE ONE,

16:26.586 --> 16:29.689
SO I KINDA DREADED SATURDAYS.

16:29.722 --> 16:32.259
[robot whirring]

16:34.394 --> 16:37.764
- WELL, I CAN PROMISE YOU--

16:37.797 --> 16:41.501
ONLY HAPPY SATURDAYS
FROM NOW ON.

16:47.640 --> 16:50.243
- ANOTHER THERAPIST?

16:50.277 --> 16:52.512
- WITH THAT ATTITUDE
WE'LL GET A LOT ACCOMPLISHED.

16:52.545 --> 16:53.780
- BUT YOU'RE THE ONE
WHO'S GOT A PROBLEM.

16:53.813 --> 16:56.616
- AND YOU DON'T?
- ONLY THE ONE YOU'RE CREATING.

16:56.649 --> 16:57.684
- OH, CHRIST!

16:57.717 --> 17:00.153
AM I LIVING
IN THIS HOUSE ALONE?

17:00.187 --> 17:02.055
- MAYBE YOU'D BE HAPPIER
IF YOU WERE.

17:02.089 --> 17:04.391
[doorbell rings]

17:04.424 --> 17:06.659
- I'LL GET IT.

17:08.695 --> 17:11.464
- MEET MY LATEST TRICK.

17:11.498 --> 17:13.133
- AH.

17:13.166 --> 17:14.701
I DIDN'T KNOW
YOU WERE INTO BEARS.

17:14.734 --> 17:16.536
I THOUGHT YOU PREFERRED
THE YOUNG, HAIRLESS,

17:16.569 --> 17:18.838
"NOT ADMITTED WITHOUT
A PARENT OR GUARDIAN" TYPE.

17:18.871 --> 17:22.209
- WHERE'S MY SON?
- OUR SON IS TAKING A NAP.

17:22.242 --> 17:25.078
- WELL, I THOUGHT
I'D DROP BY FOR DINNER.

17:25.112 --> 17:27.680
- IT'S 2:00
IN THE AFTERNOON.

17:27.714 --> 17:29.516
- THEN I'LL JUST HANG OUT.
- HANG OUT?

17:29.549 --> 17:31.284
SINCE WHEN DID YOU "HANG OUT"
WITH THE LIKES OF US?

17:31.318 --> 17:33.286
- SINCE MICHAEL'S NO LONGER
IN THE PICTURE.

17:33.320 --> 17:35.288
- IT'S JUST AS WELL.

17:35.322 --> 17:38.125
MIKEY AND I WERE HOLDING ON
TO EACH OTHER FOR TOO LONG.

17:38.158 --> 17:39.292
I MEAN,
WHEN YOU THINK ABOUT IT,

17:39.326 --> 17:40.293
WHAT DO WE EVEN
HAVE IN COMMON?

17:40.327 --> 17:42.795
- YOUR LIVES.

17:42.829 --> 17:45.098
- ASIDE FROM THAT.

17:45.132 --> 17:47.800
ANYWAYS, IT WORKED OUT
FOR THE BEST.

17:47.834 --> 17:49.369
THANKS TO MY
DIVINE INTERVENTION,

17:49.402 --> 17:51.304
HE'S WITH
THE GOOD DOCTOR NOW--

17:51.338 --> 17:52.572
WHERE HE BELONGS.

17:52.605 --> 17:55.708
- LOOK, I GUESS
IT'S NOT TOO LATE.

17:55.742 --> 17:57.144
- FOR WHAT?

17:57.177 --> 17:58.745
- TO FIX THINGS.

17:58.778 --> 18:01.781
- SOME THINGS ARE BETTER
LEFT BROKEN.

18:03.850 --> 18:07.520
SO. WHAT DO YOU SAY
WE PLAY A LITTLE SCRABBLE?

18:10.157 --> 18:11.824
- I GOT THIS
OFF THE INTERNET,

18:11.858 --> 18:13.460
WAIT'LL YOU HEAR IT.

18:13.493 --> 18:16.329
"TEN WAYS TO KNOW
IF YOUR HUSBAND'S GAY."

18:16.363 --> 18:17.597
[laughs]

18:17.630 --> 18:19.732
NUMBER ONE: "AT YOUR WEDDING,

18:19.766 --> 18:22.469
HE KISSES THE BEST MAN
INSTEAD OF YOU."

18:22.502 --> 18:23.736
[laughter]

18:23.770 --> 18:25.605
NUMBER TWO:
"FOR YOUR BIRTHDAY,

18:25.638 --> 18:27.174
"HE BRINGS YOU FLOWERS,

18:27.207 --> 18:28.875
AND ARRANGES THEM."

18:28.908 --> 18:30.610
[laughter]

18:30.643 --> 18:33.313
NUMBER THREE--

18:33.346 --> 18:34.347
WHAT'S THE MATTER?

18:34.381 --> 18:35.615
YOU'RE NOT LAUGHING.

18:35.648 --> 18:38.218
- I DON'T THINK IT'S VERY FUNNY,
THAT'S ALL.

18:38.251 --> 18:40.520
- WELL, I THINK IT'S A SCREAM.

18:40.553 --> 18:43.356
DON'T YOU, MIKE?

18:43.390 --> 18:46.359
- UH, I WASN'T
REALLY LISTENING.

18:50.530 --> 18:52.732
- YOU'RE ENTITLED
TO THINK WHATEVER YOU WANT,

18:52.765 --> 18:54.601
AND SO AM I.

18:54.634 --> 18:57.504
AND WHAT I THINK IS THAT

18:57.537 --> 18:58.905
PEOPLE WHO LAUGH AT JOKES

18:58.938 --> 19:00.507
THAT MAKE FUN
OF OTHER PEOPLE,

19:00.540 --> 19:02.875
WHOEVER THEY ARE,

19:02.909 --> 19:05.812
ARE IGNORANT AND CRUEL.

19:08.548 --> 19:11.518
- WHAT'S HER PROBLEM?

19:19.826 --> 19:22.595
- MR. NOVOTNY?

19:22.629 --> 19:24.331
- YES, TRACY?

19:24.364 --> 19:26.699
- I WANTED
TO GIVE YOU SOMETHING.

19:26.733 --> 19:28.268
- WHAT?

19:28.301 --> 19:30.870
- TWO WEEKS NOTICE.

19:30.903 --> 19:35.608
I GOT A JOB
AT THE BIG DOLLAR MART.

19:35.642 --> 19:38.611
I SHOULD REALLY GET BACK,
MY BREAK'S OVER.

19:47.320 --> 19:50.257
[indistinct chatter]

19:53.726 --> 19:55.795
- I'M NOT INTERESTED.

19:57.530 --> 19:58.731
- BRIAN, HEY.

19:58.765 --> 20:00.500
HOW'S IT GOING?

20:00.533 --> 20:02.502
- WHAT DO YOU WANT?

20:02.535 --> 20:04.904
- TO TELL YOU WHAT A GREAT TIME
WE HAD LAST NIGHT.

20:04.937 --> 20:09.309
- I WAS BORED
OUT OF MY FUCKING MIND.

20:09.342 --> 20:10.777
- YEAH, WELL, UH, YOU KNOW,

20:10.810 --> 20:11.978
THAT'S THE SIGN
OF TRUE FRIENDSHIP,

20:12.011 --> 20:13.446
YOU KNOW, THAT IT CAN,
UH, ACCOMMODATE

20:13.480 --> 20:15.382
VASTLY DIVERGENT
POINTS OF VIEW.

20:15.415 --> 20:17.450
[chuckles]

20:20.487 --> 20:23.356
- I'M NOT INTERESTED.

20:26.559 --> 20:28.261
- YOU KNOW, UH,
JUST OUT OF CURIOSITY,

20:28.295 --> 20:31.631
HOW MANY GUYS
HIT ON YOU A NIGHT?

20:31.664 --> 20:33.333
- GIVE OR TAKE, 112.

20:33.366 --> 20:34.734
I DON'T KNOW.

20:34.767 --> 20:36.436
- AMAZING.

20:36.469 --> 20:38.805
AND I ONLY NEED ONE.

20:41.574 --> 20:44.877
- I'M NOT INTERESTED.

20:44.911 --> 20:49.015
- [clears throat]
UH, EXCUSE ME. UM--

20:49.048 --> 20:51.418
YOU KNOW, UH,

20:51.451 --> 20:54.053
TAX SEASON IS COMING UP,
AND, UH,

20:54.086 --> 20:57.524
YOU DON'T WANT TO GET CAUGHT
WITH YOUR PANTS DOWN.

21:07.434 --> 21:10.002
- I'M MATT.

21:10.036 --> 21:12.071
- OF COURSE YOU ARE.

21:12.104 --> 21:16.042
YOU'RE ALWAYS MATT,
OR SCOTT,

21:16.075 --> 21:18.645
OR--OR TODD,

21:18.678 --> 21:22.515
OR SOME OTHER WONDERFUL,
ONE-SYLLABLE NAME.

21:22.549 --> 21:23.816
- I'D OFFER
TO BUY YOU A DRINK,

21:23.850 --> 21:25.852
BUT SOMETHING TELLS ME
YOU DON'T NEED ANOTHER.

21:25.885 --> 21:28.721
- SOMETHING TELLS ME...

21:28.755 --> 21:32.825
YOU MIGHT BE RIGHT.

21:32.859 --> 21:34.761
NOW, IF YOU'LL EXCUSE ME,

21:34.794 --> 21:36.896
I'M GOING TO GO HOME.

21:36.929 --> 21:38.498
IT'S ALWAYS NICER
TO VOMIT

21:38.531 --> 21:41.468
IN YOUR OWN TOILET.

21:42.802 --> 21:46.539
- MAYBE I BETTER
GIVE YOU A HAND.

21:46.573 --> 21:48.007
- THANK YOU.

21:48.040 --> 21:50.410
- MAYBE YOU'RE JUST
REEVALUATING YOUR LIFE,

21:50.443 --> 21:51.678
QUESTIONING YOUR CHOICES,

21:51.711 --> 21:54.547
WONDERING IF THERE'S
SOMETHING BETTER.

21:54.581 --> 21:56.048
- YEAH.

21:56.082 --> 21:58.585
YEAH, THAT'S IT EXACTLY.

21:58.618 --> 22:00.353
HOW'D YOU KNOW?

22:00.387 --> 22:03.089
- 'CAUSE I'VE SEEN THE LIGHT.

22:03.122 --> 22:04.724
AND SEEING HOW MISERABLE
YOU LOOKED AT THE BAR

22:04.757 --> 22:07.727
MADE ME THINK MAYBE
YOU NEEDED TO SEE IT TOO.

22:09.862 --> 22:11.030
- WHAT'S THIS?

22:11.063 --> 22:13.600
- A GROUP I BELONG TO.

22:13.633 --> 22:16.403
- HMM, I DON'T DO VERY WELL
IN GROUPS.

22:16.436 --> 22:18.571
I GOT THROWN OUT
OF THE CUB SCOUTS FIRST WEEK.

22:18.605 --> 22:20.973
I MADE A FABULOUS NECKLACE
OUT OF SLIP KNOTS.

22:21.007 --> 22:23.109
- EVERYONE'S WELCOME
IN THIS GROUP.

22:23.142 --> 22:25.011
AND IT'S ALL PEOPLE LIKE US.

22:25.044 --> 22:26.646
- LIKE US?

22:26.679 --> 22:29.816
- PEOPLE WHO ARE QUESTIONING
AND EVALUATING.

22:29.849 --> 22:32.752
WHY DON'T YOU COME
TO ONE OF OUR MEETINGS?

22:32.785 --> 22:34.487
ALL YOU'VE GOT TO LOSE
IS YOUR PAIN.

22:34.521 --> 22:37.490
[techno music]

22:37.524 --> 22:45.498
*

22:47.567 --> 22:48.835
- YOU MAKE A LOT OF TIPS.

22:48.868 --> 22:50.803
- THAT'S 'CAUSE I'M CUTE.

22:50.837 --> 22:52.805
- YEAH, AND CONCEITED.

22:52.839 --> 22:55.141
- I COULD FUCK PRACTICALLY
ANYONE I WANTED.

22:55.174 --> 22:58.010
- SO WHY DON'T YOU?

23:00.813 --> 23:01.948
[sighs]

23:01.981 --> 23:03.416
NEVER MIND.

23:03.450 --> 23:06.486
THE ANSWER JUST WALKED
IN THE DOOR.

23:06.519 --> 23:07.720
- HEY.

23:07.754 --> 23:09.155
HOW'S IT GOING?

23:09.188 --> 23:11.157
- WHAT, YOU ACTUALLY
WANT TO KNOW?

23:11.190 --> 23:15.895
- WELL, I ASKED, DIDN'T I?

23:15.928 --> 23:17.630
- EVERYTHING'S FINE.

23:17.664 --> 23:20.166
- GOOD.

23:20.199 --> 23:23.536
WHAT ARE YOU DOING TONIGHT?

23:23.570 --> 23:25.037
- HUH?

23:25.071 --> 23:29.041
- ARE THESE PARTICULARLY
HARD QUESTIONS?

23:29.075 --> 23:33.112
DO YOU WANT TO COME OVER
AFTER WORK?

23:33.145 --> 23:35.815
- REALLY?

23:35.848 --> 23:37.784
SURE.

23:37.817 --> 23:40.653
I'LL HAVE A TURKEY SANDWICH
ON WHOLE GRAIN.

23:40.687 --> 23:43.623
NO MAYO. TO GO.

23:45.892 --> 23:47.059
- DO YOU REALIZE
THIS IS THE FIRST TIME

23:47.093 --> 23:48.661
HE'S EVER ASKED ME
TO COME OVER?

23:48.695 --> 23:51.664
- SO WHAT
DO YOU THINK IT MEANS?

23:58.571 --> 24:00.640
- IT MEANS HE MISSES MICHAEL.

24:00.673 --> 24:02.809
- [sighs]
ARE THOSE GUYS REALLY

24:02.842 --> 24:05.545
NEVER GOING
TO TALK TO EACH OTHER AGAIN?

24:05.578 --> 24:07.580
- IT LOOKS THAT WAY.

24:07.614 --> 24:10.683
- SO WHY DON'T YOU
TALK TO HIM?

24:10.717 --> 24:11.951
- ME?

24:11.984 --> 24:13.686
- WELL, I THOUGHT
YOU LOVED BRIAN.

24:13.720 --> 24:15.688
AND YOU'RE STAYING
IN MICHAEL'S BEDROOM,

24:15.722 --> 24:19.225
WHICH MAKES YOU, LIKE,
THE MISSING LINK.

24:19.258 --> 24:22.128
WELL, GO ON.

24:26.999 --> 24:28.701
- HEY, BOY WONDER, UH--

24:28.735 --> 24:31.103
A COUPLE OF LEMON SQUARES.
TO GO.

24:31.137 --> 24:34.106
- SURE.

24:42.749 --> 24:46.118
AREN'T YOU
GOING TO TALK TO HIM?

24:46.152 --> 24:47.920
- WHAT FOR?

24:47.954 --> 24:49.088
- HE'S RIGHT THERE.

24:49.121 --> 24:52.058
- STAY THE FUCK OUT OF IT.

25:06.005 --> 25:07.239
- YOU GUYS SHOULD TALK.

25:07.273 --> 25:09.008
- YOU SHOULD
MIND YOUR OWN BUSINESS.

25:09.041 --> 25:10.543
- BUT HE'S YOUR BEST FRIEND.

25:10.577 --> 25:12.178
- JUST GIVE ME
THE LEMON SQUARES.

25:12.211 --> 25:15.181
- HEY, WHERE'S MY ORDER?

25:17.784 --> 25:21.153
- THIS IS A TURKEY SANDWICH.

25:21.187 --> 25:24.190
- THESE ARE LEMON SQUARES.

25:33.666 --> 25:35.902
- [whispers]
SORRY.

25:42.141 --> 25:44.210
- HONEY, I'M HOME!

25:44.243 --> 25:46.145
GOD, I HAVE ALWAYS
WANTED TO SAY THAT.

25:46.178 --> 25:48.214
- HEY, I THOUGHT
I HEARD YOU COMING IN.

25:48.247 --> 25:49.315
- MM.

25:49.348 --> 25:51.350
- AND HONEY,
YOU REALLY ARE HOME.

25:51.383 --> 25:54.020
- YEAH, I PICKED THESE UP
FOR DESSERT.

25:54.053 --> 25:57.023
HOW WAS THE--
GAME?

25:59.692 --> 26:01.928
- PENGUINS LOST IN OVERTIME.

26:01.961 --> 26:05.031
THESE ARE BEAUTIFUL.

26:05.064 --> 26:07.667
- THE PLACE LOOKS DIFFERENT.

26:07.700 --> 26:10.670
- YEAH, WELL, I--

26:10.703 --> 26:12.805
I PUT A FEW THINGS AWAY.

26:12.839 --> 26:16.676
- YEAH, LIKE, ALL MY STUFF.

26:16.709 --> 26:20.146
- OH, WELL, IT WAS A BIT, UH,
CLUTTERED.

26:23.049 --> 26:23.883
HOW WAS YOUR DAY?

26:23.916 --> 26:26.619
- MY DAY?
MY--MY DAY WAS COMPELLING,

26:26.653 --> 26:27.586
CHOCK FULL OF EVENT.

26:27.620 --> 26:30.322
WE GOT A NEW HANDICAP RAMP,
AND FAT MARLEY

26:30.356 --> 26:33.359
REGALED US WITH HER WITTY
REPERTOIRE OF FAG JOKES.

26:33.392 --> 26:35.862
- [chuckles]
WHAT DID YOU DO?

26:35.895 --> 26:37.964
- I TOLD HER I'M
AN OUT-AND-PROUD HOMOSEXUAL,

26:37.997 --> 26:40.099
AND IF SHE DOESN'T LIKE IT,
SHE CAN SUCK MY DICK.

26:40.132 --> 26:42.735
- [laughs]

26:42.769 --> 26:45.071
- I DIDN'T DO ANYTHING.

26:45.104 --> 26:46.372
TRACY DID.

26:46.405 --> 26:49.008
SHE STOOD RIGHT UP TO HER.

26:49.041 --> 26:53.045
- GOOD. SO SHE'S
STILL YOUR FRIEND.

26:53.079 --> 26:55.982
- I WOULDN'T SAY THAT.

26:56.015 --> 27:00.853
- HEY, WELL, ONE GOOD THING
CAME OUT OF WHAT BRIAN DID.

27:00.887 --> 27:04.423
IT MADE YOU REALIZE
THAT YOU BELONG HERE WITH ME.

27:04.456 --> 27:07.860
TAKE OFF YOUR JACKET,
GET READY FOR DINNER.

27:20.106 --> 27:21.841
- ONE SPOONFUL LEFT.

27:21.874 --> 27:23.409
YOU WANT IT?

27:23.442 --> 27:26.846
- NO, IT'LL MEAN 10 MORE MINUTES
ON THE STAIRMASTER.

27:26.879 --> 27:28.014
- MM, COME ON.

27:28.047 --> 27:31.250
I WANT TO SEE YOU
LICK IT OFF THE SPOON.

27:45.998 --> 27:49.401
MMM, ICE CREAM KISS.

27:51.137 --> 27:53.172
YOU SHOULD EAT MORE,
YOU KNOW.

27:53.205 --> 27:56.008
MY MOM SAYS
YOU'RE TOO SKINNY.

27:56.042 --> 27:58.077
- YOUR MOM?
- MM-HMM.

27:58.110 --> 28:02.214
SHE DOESN'T COMPLETELY HATE YOU,
YOU KNOW.

28:02.248 --> 28:04.316
I TOLD HER YOU WERE
ALWAYS SKINNY,

28:04.350 --> 28:06.218
EVEN WHEN YOU WERE
IN HIGH SCHOOL.

28:06.252 --> 28:07.720
- [chuckles]
YOU DON'T KNOW

28:07.754 --> 28:09.188
WHAT I LOOKED LIKE
IN HIGH SCHOOL.

28:09.221 --> 28:11.824
- I LIVE IN MICHAEL'S OLD ROOM,
REMEMBER?

28:11.858 --> 28:14.326
WITH ALL HIS
OLD HIGH SCHOOL YEARBOOKS,

28:14.360 --> 28:15.962
PICTURES OF YOU.

28:15.995 --> 28:17.396
[chuckles]

28:17.429 --> 28:18.831
YOU WERE A GEEK.

28:18.865 --> 28:20.366
- I WAS NEVER A GEEK.

28:20.399 --> 28:22.769
- THEN EXPLAIN CHEMISTRY CLUB.

28:22.802 --> 28:24.003
- THAT'S WHERE I LEARNED
TO BUILD

28:24.036 --> 28:25.404
THE BOMB
TO BLOW UP THE SCHOOL.

28:25.437 --> 28:27.774
- [laughs]

28:27.807 --> 28:30.209
- BUT MIKEY
TALKED ME OUT OF IT.

28:30.242 --> 28:33.112
- GOOD THING HE WAS AROUND.

28:34.881 --> 28:36.816
I BET YOU WISH
HE WAS HERE RIGHT NOW.

28:36.849 --> 28:38.450
- WOULD YOU SHUT THE FUCK UP
ABOUT HIM?

28:38.484 --> 28:39.886
- [chuckles]

28:39.919 --> 28:42.088
I BET YOU'RE
SECRETLY WISHING

28:42.121 --> 28:43.990
THAT THE PHONE WOULD RING
AND IT WOULD BE HIM.

28:44.023 --> 28:46.993
I SAID SHUT THE FUCK UP.

28:50.562 --> 28:53.833
HIS LIFE, IT WAS JUST
GOING TO HANG THERE

28:53.866 --> 28:57.036
LIKE SOME SHIRT
IN THE CLOSET YOU NEVER WEAR.

28:57.069 --> 28:58.905
- SO YOU PUSHED HIM AWAY.

28:58.938 --> 29:01.207
- IT WAS THE ONLY
COURSE OF ACTION.

29:01.240 --> 29:03.542
- YEAH, BUT NOW HE HATES YOU.

29:03.575 --> 29:07.513
- THAT'S OKAY.
AS LONG AS MIKEY'S HAPPY.

29:07.546 --> 29:11.150
- GOD, YOU MUST
REALLY LOVE HIM.

29:14.020 --> 29:15.387
- I THINK IT'S TIME
FOR YOU TO GO.

29:15.421 --> 29:18.290
- [chuckles]
IT ALWAYS IS.

29:20.459 --> 29:23.695
LUCKILY, YOU CAN'T
PUSH ME AWAY.

29:27.566 --> 29:30.536
I'M ON TO YOU.

29:44.483 --> 29:47.486
[techno music]

29:47.519 --> 29:55.461
*

30:04.036 --> 30:07.139
- EMMETT, YOU CAME.
IT'S GOOD TO SEE YOU.

30:07.173 --> 30:09.308
- HI, I'M TY,
AND I HAVE SEEN THE LIGHT.

30:09.341 --> 30:10.576
- COME ON, LET'S GO.

30:10.609 --> 30:12.378
all: HI, TY.

30:12.411 --> 30:14.914
- OUR FIRST SPEAKER TONIGHT
IS GINGER.

30:14.947 --> 30:17.216
AND SHE WAS FORMERLY
IN THE DARK,

30:17.249 --> 30:18.918
BUT NOW SHE'S...

30:18.951 --> 30:23.455
all: SEEN THE LIGHT.

30:23.489 --> 30:26.358
- BELIEVE IT OR NOT, I, UH,
USED TO BE A LESBIAN.

30:26.392 --> 30:27.927
- USED TO BE?
- SHH.

30:27.960 --> 30:31.497
- BUT THANKS TO TY
AND EVERY BEAUTIFUL PERSON HERE,

30:31.530 --> 30:34.100
I'VE SHED
MY FORMER CORRUPT SELF

30:34.133 --> 30:38.905
AND BECOME THE NEW,
PURIFIED HETEROSEXUAL ME.

30:38.938 --> 30:43.609
[cheers and applause]

30:43.642 --> 30:45.111
- AS YOU CAN SEE,

30:45.144 --> 30:47.313
THE ONLY THING THAT COMES OUT
HERE IS THE TRUTH.

30:47.346 --> 30:49.181
- YOU DIDN'T TELL ME THIS
WAS A COMEDY CLUB.

30:49.215 --> 30:50.416
- EMMETT.

30:50.449 --> 30:53.652
- I CAN TELL YOU,
AND GINGER CAN TELL YOU,

30:53.685 --> 30:56.622
THAT WHAT YOU'RE ALL HOPING
AND PRAYING FOR

30:56.655 --> 30:59.025
IS NOT AN IMPOSSIBLE DREAM.

30:59.058 --> 31:01.127
IT COULD COME TRUE FOR YOU,

31:01.160 --> 31:04.296
THE SAME WAY
IT'S COME TRUE FOR US.

31:04.330 --> 31:06.966
YOU CAN CHANGE,
YOU CAN CHANGE...

31:06.999 --> 31:09.001
all: YOU CAN CHANGE.

31:09.035 --> 31:11.870
- I'D START WITH THOSE SHOES.

31:15.274 --> 31:17.243
- YOU.

31:17.276 --> 31:19.111
- UH, M-ME?

31:19.145 --> 31:21.981
- YOU'VE GOT YOUR DOUBTS,
DON'T YOU?

31:22.014 --> 31:24.650
