A FEW QUESTIONS.

31:24.683 --> 31:27.253
DO YOU AND YOUR FRIENDS
OBSESS ABOUT YOUR BODIES

31:27.286 --> 31:29.255
AND THE BODIES OF OTHER MEN?

31:29.288 --> 31:32.224
- CHECK OUT HIS PECS.
- THEY'RE, LIKE, PERFECT.

31:32.258 --> 31:34.126
- THEY'RE, LIKE, IMPLANTS.

31:34.160 --> 31:37.263
- DO YOUR CONVERSATIONS CENTER
AROUND TRIVIALITIES?

31:37.296 --> 31:40.032
SUCH AS...MOVIE STARS?

31:40.066 --> 31:42.634
- DID YOU HEAR THAT CHER
HAD HER PUSSY TIGHTENED?

31:42.668 --> 31:44.136
- WHERE'D YOU READ THAT?

31:44.170 --> 31:45.972
THE ENQUIRER
OR POPULAR MECHANICS?

31:46.005 --> 31:49.675
- ARE YOUR DAYS AND NIGHTS SPENT
AT THE GYM AND IN BARS?

31:49.708 --> 31:52.711
GOING HOME WITH MEN WHOSE NAMES
YOU DON'T EVEN KNOW?

31:52.744 --> 31:57.083
- SO HE'S COMING AND HE'S GOING,
"FRED, FRED!"

31:57.116 --> 31:59.151
- [laughs]
FRED? WHO'S FRED?

31:59.185 --> 32:02.154
- IF SO, MAYBE YOU SHOULD
ASK YOURSELF,

32:02.188 --> 32:04.957
"IS THIS THE LIFE I WANT
FOR ME?"

32:04.991 --> 32:09.528
"IS THIS THE LIFE GOD WANTS
FOR ME?"

32:09.561 --> 32:14.033
"IS THERE A BETTER LIFE?"

32:15.434 --> 32:17.169
- YOU'RE LOOKING
FOR SOMETHING?

32:17.203 --> 32:19.471
- YEAH, MY BEACH BALL
ALARM CLOCK.

32:23.375 --> 32:25.311
- THIS CLOCK IS FROM

32:25.344 --> 32:29.715
THE MUSEUM OF MODERN ART
DESIGN COLLECTION.

32:29.748 --> 32:31.550
- I THOUGHT YOU SAID
THIS IS MY PLACE TOO.

32:31.583 --> 32:33.285
- IT IS.

32:33.319 --> 32:37.156
- WELL, HOW COME I DON'T SEE
ANY OF MY THINGS?

32:41.193 --> 32:44.296
- MICHAEL, UH, YOU KNOW,
YOUR THINGS...

32:44.330 --> 32:45.998
YOUR TOYS?
THEY'RE, THEY'RE...

32:46.032 --> 32:48.467
THEY'RE CUTE,
THEY'RE CUTE LIKE YOU.

32:48.500 --> 32:50.702
BUT YOU KNOW, THEY S--

32:50.736 --> 32:56.142
THEY SORT OF DON'T BELONG.

32:56.175 --> 32:58.577
LET ME EXPLAIN IT
BY SAYING...

32:58.610 --> 33:01.480
THAT THIS
IS AN ARCHITECTURAL HOUSE.

33:01.513 --> 33:03.649
EVERYTHING HAS ITS PLACE.

33:03.682 --> 33:07.019
SO, IF YOU CLUTTER IT UP,
IT RUINS THE AESTHETIC.

33:07.053 --> 33:09.688
- OH, SO I'M
"CLUTTERING IT UP"?

33:09.721 --> 33:11.757
- NO! OH...

33:11.790 --> 33:13.359
I DIDN'T MEAN IT THAT WAY.

33:13.392 --> 33:16.228
- THEY'RE NOT JUST TOYS.

33:16.262 --> 33:18.097
OKAY, SOME OF THEM
ARE COLLECTOR'S ITEMS,

33:18.130 --> 33:19.731
LIKE MY JAPANESE ROBOTS,

33:19.765 --> 33:22.234
OR MY BAKELITE BATMOBILE.

33:22.268 --> 33:24.103
THAT WAS MADE
DURING WORLD WAR II,

33:24.136 --> 33:27.406
WHEN METAL WAS SCARCE.

33:27.439 --> 33:29.675
AND...

33:29.708 --> 33:33.445
EVEN IF THEY WERE WORTHLESS...

33:33.479 --> 33:37.116
THEY WOULD STILL
BE WORTH SOMETHING TO ME

33:37.149 --> 33:41.453
BECAUSE I LOVE THEM.

33:41.487 --> 33:45.157
I KIND OF THOUGHT
YOU KNEW THAT.

33:57.103 --> 33:58.504
- [panting]
LOOK, I JU--

33:58.537 --> 34:00.639
I JUST GOT YOUR PHONE CALL.
[stammering]

34:00.672 --> 34:02.774
I LITERALLY RAN OVER HERE.

34:02.808 --> 34:04.776
SO, WHAT IS THE EMERGENCY?

34:04.810 --> 34:06.645
- HIM.

34:06.678 --> 34:08.747
HE'S HERE EVERY DAY NOW,
SHOWING UP FOR MEALS.

34:08.780 --> 34:11.117
WE'RE SUDDENLY ONE BIG HAPPY
FUCKING FAMILY.

34:11.150 --> 34:12.684
- I DON'T KNOW.

34:12.718 --> 34:15.287
I SENSE SOME TENSION
BETWEEN YOU AND MEL.

34:15.321 --> 34:16.788
- [chuckles]

34:16.822 --> 34:19.791
WELL, SHE BLAMES ME
FOR EVERYTHING.

34:19.825 --> 34:22.528
INCLUDING YOU.
- [scoffs]

34:22.561 --> 34:25.797
- YOU SHOULD HAVE KEPT
YOUR PROMISE TO GIVE HER GUS.

34:25.831 --> 34:28.167
- IF SHE WANTS A KID,
SHE CAN HAVE ONE OF HER OWN.

34:28.200 --> 34:30.436
- NO, SHE CAN'T.

34:30.469 --> 34:32.704
GUS WAS SUPPOSED TO BE HERS
AND MINE.

34:32.738 --> 34:36.275
NOT YOURS AND MINE.

34:36.308 --> 34:37.643
- WELL, LINDSAY'S
ALWAYS COMPLAINING

34:37.676 --> 34:39.345
HE NEVER SPENDS ENOUGH TIME
WITH GUS.

34:39.378 --> 34:40.612
- OH, YOU'RE A BIG HELP.

34:40.646 --> 34:43.315
CAN'T YOU DO SOMETHING?
- LIKE WHAT?

34:43.349 --> 34:44.650
- LIKE GET HIM AND MICHAEL
BACK TOGETHER

34:44.683 --> 34:46.752
SO HE WILL LEAVE US ALONE.

34:46.785 --> 34:48.854
- ARE YOU KIDDING?
YOU EVEN MENTION MICHAEL'S NAME,

34:48.887 --> 34:50.389
HE'LL TEAR YOUR HEAD OFF.

34:50.422 --> 34:52.324
- YEAH? WELL, THAT'S WHAT
I'M ABOUT TO DO TO HIM.

34:52.358 --> 34:53.825
- SHE ALSO THINKS I'VE TURNED

34:53.859 --> 34:56.795
INTO THIS COLD,
UNRESPONSIVE BITCH.

34:56.828 --> 34:59.865
- HAVE YOU?

34:59.898 --> 35:00.866
- MAYBE A LITTLE.

35:00.899 --> 35:04.603
- WELL, THEN YOU SHOULD
FIND YOURSELF SOME NICE,

35:04.636 --> 35:06.838
FUZZY LEZZIE
WITH A THERAPIST'S LICENSE

35:06.872 --> 35:07.873
AND WORK IT OUT.

35:07.906 --> 35:10.609
- THAT'S WHAT MEL WANTS.

35:10.642 --> 35:14.213
- WHAT DO YOU WANT?

35:14.246 --> 35:16.415
- I WANT...

35:16.448 --> 35:21.787
I...
[sighs]

35:21.820 --> 35:23.322
[clears throat]

35:23.355 --> 35:24.623
I WANT A BAGEL.

35:24.656 --> 35:26.592
AND AFTER THAT, I DON'T KNOW.

35:26.625 --> 35:30.629
ALL I KNOW IS THAT...

35:30.662 --> 35:34.366
IF I TALK, I MIGHT
SAY SOMETHING I REGRET.

35:34.400 --> 35:36.502
- IT MIGHT BE GOOD FOR YOU.

35:36.535 --> 35:38.637
LET OUT SOME
OF THOSE NASTY DEMONS.

35:38.670 --> 35:39.871
- BUT I'M NOT LIKE THAT.

35:39.905 --> 35:42.908
SEE, I'M A WASP
FROM A FAMILY OF WASPS.

35:42.941 --> 35:44.910
- HMM.
- [chuckles]

35:44.943 --> 35:47.379
- TELL YOU WHAT, I'LL TAKE HIM
TO THE TEA DANCE AT WOODY'S.

35:47.413 --> 35:49.515
- GREAT IDEA.
THANKS, TEDDY.

35:49.548 --> 35:50.782
- YEAH.
- MWAH!

35:50.816 --> 35:52.651
- I'M NOT REALLY DOING IT
FOR YOU, YOU KNOW.

35:52.684 --> 35:55.187
HANGING WITH BRIAN...

35:55.221 --> 35:57.656
BEST THING THAT'S EVER HAPPENED
TO MY SEX LIFE.

35:57.689 --> 36:01.493
- [on PA] VIDEO TAPE SPECIAL
TODAY, TEN-PACK FOR--

36:01.527 --> 36:02.661
- SEE YA, MARLEY.

36:02.694 --> 36:08.200
- BYE, TRACE.

36:08.234 --> 36:10.769
- GOOD-BYE, MR. NOVOTNY.

36:13.305 --> 36:16.408
- TRACY!

36:16.442 --> 36:18.510
- YES, MR. NOVOTNY?

36:18.544 --> 36:20.812
- WOULD YOU STOP
CALLING ME THAT, PLEASE?

36:20.846 --> 36:22.781
- WHAT SHOULD I CALL YOU?

36:22.814 --> 36:26.552
- WELL, I'M SURE YOU COULD THINK
OF A FEW THINGS.

36:26.585 --> 36:28.787
- I HAVE TO GO.

36:28.820 --> 36:30.989
- YOU DON'T HAVE TO LEAVE
YOUR JOB.

36:31.022 --> 36:33.959
- IS THERE SOMETHING WRONG
WITH THE BIG DOLLAR MART?

36:33.992 --> 36:36.762
- WELL, IT'S NOT EXACTLY
THE BIG Q.

36:36.795 --> 36:42.468
- NO, BUT AT LEAST PEOPLE
SEEM HONEST THERE.

36:42.501 --> 36:44.503
YOU PROBABLY THINK THIS
IS ALL ABOUT YOU BEING GAY,

36:44.536 --> 36:46.805
DON'T YOU?

36:46.838 --> 36:51.543
WELL, I ADMIT,
IT MIGHT HAVE BEEN AT FIRST.

36:51.577 --> 36:53.612
BUT THAT'S
NOT THE POINT ANYMORE.

36:53.645 --> 36:55.847
WHETHER YOU'RE GAY
OR YOU'RE STRAIGHT,

36:55.881 --> 36:57.015
I THOUGHT WE WERE FRIENDS.

36:57.048 --> 36:58.584
- WE ARE.

36:58.617 --> 37:01.320
- WELL, FRIENDS TRUST
EACH OTHER.

37:01.353 --> 37:03.489
WHAT DID YOU THINK
WOULD HAPPEN IF YOU TOLD ME?

37:03.522 --> 37:06.992
THAT I'D TELL EVERYONE
AT THE STORE?

37:07.025 --> 37:10.329
I WOULDN'T HAVE, MIKE.

37:10.362 --> 37:12.864
DON'T YOU KNOW THAT?

37:12.898 --> 37:15.601
- I SHOULD'VE.

37:15.634 --> 37:19.571
BUT WHEN YOU SPEND YOUR ENTIRE
LIFE KEEPING IT A SECRET...

37:19.605 --> 37:22.408
WHO YOU REALLY ARE,

37:22.441 --> 37:24.376
YOU LEARN
TO STOP TRUSTING PEOPLE

37:24.410 --> 37:29.681
AND IT BECOMES SECOND NATURE.

37:29.715 --> 37:31.417
IT KILLS ME
THAT I HURT YOU, TRACE,

37:31.450 --> 37:34.986
AND I'D DO ANYTHING
TO TAKE THAT BACK.

37:35.020 --> 37:39.024
I KNOW I DON'T DESERVE
TO ASK THIS...

37:39.057 --> 37:43.362
BUT DO YOU THINK
WE COULD STILL BE FRIENDS?

37:43.395 --> 37:45.331
- DO YOU THINK
WE COULD BE FRIENDS?

37:49.568 --> 37:51.870
- WELL, WHY DON'T WE GO HAVE
A CUP OF BIG Q COFFEE

37:51.903 --> 37:54.473
AND FIND OUT?

37:54.506 --> 37:55.707
- I'D LIKE THAT.

37:55.741 --> 37:58.377
BUT I-I REALLY DO
HAVE TO GO.

37:58.410 --> 38:00.979
I HAVE A DATE.

38:01.012 --> 38:03.649
- IS HE STRAIGHT?

38:03.682 --> 38:04.783
[chuckles]

38:04.816 --> 38:07.085
[baby coos]
- [mocks cooing]

38:07.118 --> 38:09.421
[giggles]

38:13.559 --> 38:15.861
AT LAST, NOW WE HAVE THE HOUSE
TO OURSELF,

38:15.894 --> 38:17.963
ALONE.

38:21.700 --> 38:25.504
OH, BY THE WAY, JANET AND
THAT DICKHEAD HUSBAND OF HERS,

38:25.537 --> 38:28.907
THEY FINALLY SENT US A CARD
CONGRATULATING US ON GUS.

38:28.940 --> 38:31.510
